{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/2019/03/22/blender-tutorial-8-textures-part-1/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><em>In this new post of the series Blender tutorial I will talk about textures.</em></p>\n<hr>\n<p>In the <a href=\"/2019/03/21/blender-tutorial-7-materials/\">previous post of the series \"Blender tutorial\"</a> we talked about\nmaterials in Blender. In this post we will start to learn how to use textures.<br>\nAs you may already know, textures are useful to add realism to a material. We can manage textures from the texture tab\ninside the properties panel. From that panel we can create a new texture by clicking on the + button. After creating a\nnew texture, some options are displayed that let us customize how the texture looks like. The type of texture we select\nchanges the options displayed: there will be a specific section of properties for the type we choose.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/283bb263159a3447d06b8b56dd2cb2d1/c58a3/blender-create-texture.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Create a texture\"\n        title=\"Create a texture\"\n        src=\"/static/283bb263159a3447d06b8b56dd2cb2d1/0470c/blender-create-texture.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/283bb263159a3447d06b8b56dd2cb2d1/6c669/blender-create-texture.jpg 285w,\n/static/283bb263159a3447d06b8b56dd2cb2d1/882a4/blender-create-texture.jpg 570w,\n/static/283bb263159a3447d06b8b56dd2cb2d1/0470c/blender-create-texture.jpg 1140w,\n/static/283bb263159a3447d06b8b56dd2cb2d1/c58a3/blender-create-texture.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Create a texture</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>In the various section of the texture panel we have the \"influence section\". This section is very important because it\nlet us customize how the texture will affect the final material. This means that we can use textures to change not only\nthe final color of the material but also the shading components, geometry, specular highlight and so on.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2347cb8afa8d85124e662e5eeede93fc/c58a3/blender-texture-influence.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The influence section\"\n        title=\"The influence section\"\n        src=\"/static/2347cb8afa8d85124e662e5eeede93fc/0470c/blender-texture-influence.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/2347cb8afa8d85124e662e5eeede93fc/6c669/blender-texture-influence.jpg 285w,\n/static/2347cb8afa8d85124e662e5eeede93fc/882a4/blender-texture-influence.jpg 570w,\n/static/2347cb8afa8d85124e662e5eeede93fc/0470c/blender-texture-influence.jpg 1140w,\n/static/2347cb8afa8d85124e662e5eeede93fc/c58a3/blender-texture-influence.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">The influence section</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>To add the image to be used as texture we have to select the type \"Image or movie\". After that we can scroll in the\noption of the texture to the Image section and we can choose between create a new image or open an existing one.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/75d4473656078b8fe6bf5401204b9518/c58a3/blender-texture-add-image.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Add an image to a texture\"\n        title=\"Add an image to a texture\"\n        src=\"/static/75d4473656078b8fe6bf5401204b9518/0470c/blender-texture-add-image.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/75d4473656078b8fe6bf5401204b9518/6c669/blender-texture-add-image.jpg 285w,\n/static/75d4473656078b8fe6bf5401204b9518/882a4/blender-texture-add-image.jpg 570w,\n/static/75d4473656078b8fe6bf5401204b9518/0470c/blender-texture-add-image.jpg 1140w,\n/static/75d4473656078b8fe6bf5401204b9518/c58a3/blender-texture-add-image.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Add an image to a texture</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>After that we need to define the mapping of the texture on the surface. We can find this section by scrolling down in\nthe texture tab. The most important option here is \"Coordinates\". This option let us define the mapping of texture\ncoordinates on the image. By default is set to generated, that means that the coordinates are generated by blender for\nthe defaults primitives. Then there's the UV option, that maps to coordinates baked into the object.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c46803f85ba81bf428c3819d60776fcf/c58a3/blender-texture-choose-mapping.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.50877192982456%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Choose texture mapping\"\n        title=\"Choose texture mapping\"\n        src=\"/static/c46803f85ba81bf428c3819d60776fcf/0470c/blender-texture-choose-mapping.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c46803f85ba81bf428c3819d60776fcf/6c669/blender-texture-choose-mapping.jpg 285w,\n/static/c46803f85ba81bf428c3819d60776fcf/882a4/blender-texture-choose-mapping.jpg 570w,\n/static/c46803f85ba81bf428c3819d60776fcf/0470c/blender-texture-choose-mapping.jpg 1140w,\n/static/c46803f85ba81bf428c3819d60776fcf/c58a3/blender-texture-choose-mapping.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Choose texture mapping</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Remember that after an images has been selected as texture, it will not be shown in the 3D window if we choose the\ntexture visualization unless we load it in the UV editor. To do it choose UV editing layout and load the texture using\nthe open button.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/52e716c0c58b56532f9acc122ee6983b/c58a3/blender-texture-uv-load-image-for-3d-view.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The UV editor\"\n        title=\"The UV editor\"\n        src=\"/static/52e716c0c58b56532f9acc122ee6983b/0470c/blender-texture-uv-load-image-for-3d-view.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/52e716c0c58b56532f9acc122ee6983b/6c669/blender-texture-uv-load-image-for-3d-view.jpg 285w,\n/static/52e716c0c58b56532f9acc122ee6983b/882a4/blender-texture-uv-load-image-for-3d-view.jpg 570w,\n/static/52e716c0c58b56532f9acc122ee6983b/0470c/blender-texture-uv-load-image-for-3d-view.jpg 1140w,\n/static/52e716c0c58b56532f9acc122ee6983b/c58a3/blender-texture-uv-load-image-for-3d-view.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">The UV editor</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>The UV editor is the main tool to work with texture. By using it we can precisely apply a texture to an object using the\nunwrap texture tools. To do this we need first to define seams. Seams (as in sewing) are where the ends of a mesh are\nsewn together. Blender uses seams to understand where to unwrap the mesh. We can defines seams by selecting the edges we\nwant to mark and use the menu Mesh -> Edges -> Mark Seams. We can recognized seams as they are reported as red lines in\nthe 3D window.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5444d285e7e029193057d96405062b14/c58a3/blender-texture-mark-seams.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Blender texture mark seams\"\n        title=\"Blender texture mark seams\"\n        src=\"/static/5444d285e7e029193057d96405062b14/0470c/blender-texture-mark-seams.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5444d285e7e029193057d96405062b14/6c669/blender-texture-mark-seams.jpg 285w,\n/static/5444d285e7e029193057d96405062b14/882a4/blender-texture-mark-seams.jpg 570w,\n/static/5444d285e7e029193057d96405062b14/0470c/blender-texture-mark-seams.jpg 1140w,\n/static/5444d285e7e029193057d96405062b14/c58a3/blender-texture-mark-seams.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Blender texture mark seams</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>The we can unwrap the mesh by just selecting Mesh -> UV unwrap -> Unwrap. After that we can scale, translate and rotate\nthe unwrapped mesh to fit into the texture. After that we will finally see the texture on our mesh.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/19624b6ea25e2553dbe23393b184da07/c58a3/blender-texture-unwrap-1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Blender texture unwrap 1\"\n        title=\"Blender texture unwrap 1\"\n        src=\"/static/19624b6ea25e2553dbe23393b184da07/0470c/blender-texture-unwrap-1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/19624b6ea25e2553dbe23393b184da07/6c669/blender-texture-unwrap-1.jpg 285w,\n/static/19624b6ea25e2553dbe23393b184da07/882a4/blender-texture-unwrap-1.jpg 570w,\n/static/19624b6ea25e2553dbe23393b184da07/0470c/blender-texture-unwrap-1.jpg 1140w,\n/static/19624b6ea25e2553dbe23393b184da07/c58a3/blender-texture-unwrap-1.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Blender texture unwrap 1</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8f5611cd20b270908921d7cc435bd4ce/c58a3/blender-texture-unwrap-2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.50877192982456%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Blender texture unwrap b\"\n        title=\"Blender texture unwrap b\"\n        src=\"/static/8f5611cd20b270908921d7cc435bd4ce/0470c/blender-texture-unwrap-2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8f5611cd20b270908921d7cc435bd4ce/6c669/blender-texture-unwrap-2.jpg 285w,\n/static/8f5611cd20b270908921d7cc435bd4ce/882a4/blender-texture-unwrap-2.jpg 570w,\n/static/8f5611cd20b270908921d7cc435bd4ce/0470c/blender-texture-unwrap-2.jpg 1140w,\n/static/8f5611cd20b270908921d7cc435bd4ce/c58a3/blender-texture-unwrap-2.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Blender texture unwrap b</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>We can also create projection mapping using the UV projection. This basically means projecting a sphere, cylinder or a\ncube onto our project to get some rough mapping that we can tweak later. We can find UV projection under Mesh -> UV\nUnwrap -> &#x3C;Sphere/Cylinder/Cube> projection.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d75f557640129dcaa2b5d19f8ad5dd27/c58a3/blender-uv-projection.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.15789473684211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Blender uv projection\"\n        title=\"Blender uv projection\"\n        src=\"/static/d75f557640129dcaa2b5d19f8ad5dd27/0470c/blender-uv-projection.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d75f557640129dcaa2b5d19f8ad5dd27/6c669/blender-uv-projection.jpg 285w,\n/static/d75f557640129dcaa2b5d19f8ad5dd27/882a4/blender-uv-projection.jpg 570w,\n/static/d75f557640129dcaa2b5d19f8ad5dd27/0470c/blender-uv-projection.jpg 1140w,\n/static/d75f557640129dcaa2b5d19f8ad5dd27/c58a3/blender-uv-projection.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Blender uv projection</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>In the next post we will talk about other textures technique available in Blender.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Blender tutorial: textures - part 1","comments":true,"authors":["fabrizio_duroni"],"tags":["computer graphics","blender"],"date":"22 Mar 2019","description":"In this new post of the series Blender tutorial I will talk about textures.","math":false,"image":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"fullWidth","backgroundColor":"#383838","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/283bb263159a3447d06b8b56dd2cb2d1/139a5/blender-create-texture.jpg","srcSet":"/static/283bb263159a3447d06b8b56dd2cb2d1/e592c/blender-create-texture.jpg 750w,\n/static/283bb263159a3447d06b8b56dd2cb2d1/47c63/blender-create-texture.jpg 1080w,\n/static/283bb263159a3447d06b8b56dd2cb2d1/70aa3/blender-create-texture.jpg 1366w,\n/static/283bb263159a3447d06b8b56dd2cb2d1/139a5/blender-create-texture.jpg 1500w","sizes":"100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/283bb263159a3447d06b8b56dd2cb2d1/f06bf/blender-create-texture.webp 750w,\n/static/283bb263159a3447d06b8b56dd2cb2d1/76e19/blender-create-texture.webp 1080w,\n/static/283bb263159a3447d06b8b56dd2cb2d1/1235f/blender-create-texture.webp 1366w,\n/static/283bb263159a3447d06b8b56dd2cb2d1/8c8a6/blender-create-texture.webp 1500w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"100vw"}]},"width":1,"height":0.632}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/2019/03/22/blender-tutorial-8-textures-part-1/","readingTime":{"text":"3 min read"}}},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"author":"Fabrizio Duroni"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2019/03/22/blender-tutorial-8-textures-part-1/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3076394108","379746230","4028829600","630498219"]}